  akka-stream 2910 tps://akka.io API documentation API (Scaladoc) API (Javadoc) Forums Lightbend Discuss akka/akka Gitter channel Release notes akka.io blog Issues Github issues Sources https://github.com/akka/akka-http The Akka HTTP modules implement a full server- and client-side HTTP stack on top of akka-actor and akka-stream . It’s not a web-framework but rather a more general toolkit for providing and consuming HTTP-based services. While interaction with a browser is of course also in scope it is not the primary focus of Akka HTTP. Akka HTTP follows a rather open design and many times offers several different API levels for “doing the same thing”. You get to pick the API level of abstraction that is most suitable for your application. This means that, if you have trouble achieving something using a high-level API, there’s a good chance that you can get it done with a low-level API, which offers more f
  2.7.0 6448 u come from Play and want to try Akka HTTP, we collected a side-by-side comparison to show how some Play routing features map to the Akka HTTP routing DSL. Using Akka HTTP Akka HTTP is provided as independent modules from Akka itself under its own release cycle. Akka HTTP is compatible with Akka >= 2.7.0 and future Akka 2.x versions that are released during the lifetime of Akka HTTP 10.4.x. The modules, however, do not depend on akka-actor or akka-stream , so the user is required to choose an Akka version to run against and add a manual dependency to akka-stream of the chosen version. sbt val AkkaVersion = "2.7.0" val AkkaHttpVersion = "10.5.3" libraryDependencies ++= Seq( "com.typesafe.akka" %% "akka-actor-typed" % AkkaVersion, "com.typesafe.akka" %% "akka-stream" % AkkaVersion, "com.typesafe.akka" %% "akka-http" % AkkaHttpVersion ) Gradle def versions = [ AkkaVersion: "2.7.0", ScalaBin
