ream since both are required. I’ll likely need to include both dependencies while ensuring they’re versioned correctly—AkkaVersion 2.7.0—and set them to `testImplementation`. There's also the consideration about test setup to avoid blocking.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying test setup guidance**\\n\\nI need to ensure that I'm addressing the \\\"test-code setup guidance\\\" without just repeating what's already been determined. The prompt asks for environment or system property guidance, as well as any test setup instructions I may have. If there's no environment aspect but I do have test setup advice, I should definitely include that information. It’s important to be clear and helpful, while also not being unnecessarily repetitive.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating risks in dependencies**\\n\\nI might need to consider potential risks regarding the Akka dependencies in the latest documentation, particularly for version 2.10 that requires a secure repo with a token. The version 2.7.0 from Maven Central seems acceptable, but I need to note that native image support for Akka 2.7.0 can have thread sensitivity. I should verify local dependency resolution without modifying any repos. Using `gradle` or Python for parsing the POM file might be beneficial, ensuring a valid JSON output without unnecessary speculation.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying agent guidance setup**\\n\\nI need to summarize my reasoning. It's clear that I shouldn't restate deterministic entries as guidance—so agent guidance shouldn't suggest adding dependencies. Instead, it can guide on using an in-process localhost server or ephemeral ports while terminating the ActorSystem. The question asks about environment variables and system properties, but we don’t require any. We do need to consider test-code setup, likely focused on creating and shutting down the ActorSystem, which is pretty standard. I can keep agent guidance minimal to avoid confusion.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Researching Akka native image requirements**\\n\\nI’m wondering if the tests should set a local property. I should look into the native image documentation for Akka to see if it requires `-Dakka.actor.provider=local`. This seems like an important detail to confirm for proper configuration. If I can find this in the documentation, it could clarify what settings are necessary, ensuring everything functions smoothly. I'll take some time to explore the relevant documentation.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Cyozd0R7QDyrfMlxTPb9vi8F|fc_032bff6b317b5a74016a3f8a06d500819482efd5437e18cecb", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request,re,html\nurls=['https://doc.akka.io/libraries/akka-core/2.7.0/additional/native-image.html','https://doc.akka.io/libraries/akka-http/10.5.3/server-side/server-https-support.html']\nfor url in urls:\n print('\\n---',url)\n try:\n  data=urllib.request.urlopen(urllib.request.Request(url,headers={'User-Agent':'Mozilla/5.0'}),timeout=20).read().decode('utf-8','ignore')\n  text=html.unescape(re.sub('\\s+',' ',re.sub('<[^>]+>',' ',data)))\n  for term in ['system property','-D', 'native-image', 'akka.', 'reflect']:\n   i=text.lower().find(term.lower()); print(term,i, text[max(0,i-300):i+700] if i>=0 else '')\n except Exception as e: print('ERR',e)\nPY", "timeout": 60}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1600, "output": 1205, "cacheRead": 18432, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 21237, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782548982716, "responseId": "resp_032bff6b317b5a74016a3f89f718c481948139b6c91f5ff934"}}
